---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="CLI — The Yips"
  description="Access your golf stats from the terminal. Install the yips CLI via Homebrew and pull your rounds, stats, and strokes gained data from any terminal."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="tag">CLI</p>
        <h1>Your stats,<br /><em>in the terminal.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Pull your rounds, stats, and strokes gained data from any terminal.
          Pipe it into a spreadsheet, feed it to an AI, or just read it over coffee.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Install -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Install</h2>

        <h3>Homebrew <span class="platform-badge">macOS / Linux</span></h3>
        <pre class="terminal"><code>brew install --cask undeadC0rp/tap/yips</code></pre>

        <h3>Windows <span class="platform-badge">manual install</span></h3>
        <p>Download the latest <code class="inline">yips_windows_amd64.zip</code> (Intel) or <code class="inline">yips_windows_arm64.zip</code> (ARM) from the <a class="inline-link" href="https://github.com/undeadC0rp/theyips-cli/releases/latest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">releases page</a>, extract, and add <code class="inline">yips.exe</code> to your PATH.</p>

        <h3>Getting started</h3>
        <p>Authenticate with your Google account. This opens a browser for OAuth — credentials are stored at <code class="inline">~/.config/yips/credentials.json</code> and refreshed automatically.</p>
        <pre class="terminal"><code>yips login</code></pre>
      </section>

      <!-- Commands -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Commands</h2>

        <!-- rounds -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips rounds</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">List all your rounds</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>ID        DATE        COURSE            HOLES  SCORE  +/-
a1b2c3d4  2024-11-03  Pine Valley GC    18     82     +10
b5c6d7e8  2024-10-20  Cypress Creek CC  18     79     +7</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- round -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips round &lt;id&gt;</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Hole-by-hole scorecard with strokes gained</span>
          </div>
          <p class="cmd-note">Use the short ID prefix shown in <code class="inline">yips rounds</code>. Add <code class="inline">--profile hcp_10</code> to compare against a different benchmark.</p>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>Pine Valley GC  ·  2024-11-03  ·  18 holes
Rating: 74.5  ·  Slope: 142  ·  Par: 72
SG benchmark: tour_pro (putting: scratch)

HOLE  PAR  SCORE  +/-   PUTTS  FIR  GIR  SG:TEE  SG:APP  SG:ARG  SG:PUTT
1     4    5      +1    2      Y    N    -       -       -       -0.78
2     3    4      +1    2      -    N    -       -       -       -0.42
4     4    4      E     1      Y    N    -0.21   -1.00   +0.18   +0.02
5     4    3      -1    1      Y    Y    -0.06   +0.95   -       +0.00
───   ───  ─────  ────  ─────  ───  ───  ──────  ──────  ──────  ───────
TOT   72   82     +10   34     9/14 10/18 +1.20  -3.41   +0.18   -1.18</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- hole -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips hole &lt;id&gt; &lt;hole&gt;</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Shot-by-shot chart for a single hole</span>
          </div>
          <p class="cmd-note">Requires shot data recorded in the mobile app. Each bar shows where the shot started relative to the hole length.</p>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>Hole 5  Par 4  350yds  Score: 3 (-1)

         0                        175                  350yds
         ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TEE    1 █████████████████████████████░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░  200yds   FWY
APP    2 ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░███████████████████████  155yds   FWY
PUTT   3 ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░●  Gimmie</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- stats -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips stats</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Aggregate stats across all rounds</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>12 rounds  ·  Last played 2024-11-03

METRIC           VALUE
Scoring average  84.2
Average +/-      +12.2
Putts / round    33.1
Fairways hit     58%
GIR              38%
Up & down        32%

PAR  HOLES  AVG SCORE
3    72     3.42
4    216    4.61
5    72     5.38</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- stats id -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips stats &lt;id&gt;</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Full breakdown for a single round</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>Pine Valley GC  ·  2024-11-03
SG benchmark: tour_pro (putting: scratch)

METRIC                VALUE
Score                 82 (+10)
Putts                 34
Fairways hit          9/14 (64%)
GIR                   10/18 (56%)
Up & down             4/8 (50%)
SG: Off-the-Tee       +1.20 (10 holes)
SG: Approach          -3.41 (12 holes)
SG: Around-the-Green  +0.18 (3 holes)
SG: Putting           -1.18 (16 holes)

SCORING  COUNT
Birdie   2
Par      8
Bogey    6
Double   2</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- clubs -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips clubs</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Distance and strokes gained per club</span>
          </div>
          <p class="cmd-note">SG per club is aggregated from shot-level data. Add <code class="inline">--json</code> to emit raw data for further analysis.</p>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>CLUB               BRAND    SHOTS  AVG  MIN  MAX  SG TOTAL  SG/SHOT
Driver KING LTDx   Cobra      20   264  198  328    +7.47    +0.498
7 Wood             Cobra      10   178   40  234    +1.15    +0.128
7i                 Takomo      5   158  140  171    -0.65    -0.325
Putter             L.A.B.      0     -    -    -   -14.29    -0.265</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- holes -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips holes &lt;course&gt;</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Per-hole breakdown across all rounds at a course</span>
          </div>
          <p class="cmd-note">Accepts a partial, case-insensitive course name. Holes are flagged (<code class="inline">*</code>) when you're averaging +1.0 or worse and GIR is below 30% across 3+ rounds.</p>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>Course: Riverbend GC  ·  3 rounds

HOLE  PAR  RNDS  AVG +/-  FIR%  GIR%  TEE CLUB  ⚠
1     4    3     +0.7     67%   44%   Driver
7     4    3     +1.3     33%    0%   Driver     *

* Club selection review:
  Hole 7 (par 4) — Driver 3× (avg +1.3) — consider a shorter club off the tee</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- notes -->
        <div class="cmd-block">
          <div class="cmd-header">
            <span class="cmd-name">yips notes</span>
            <span class="cmd-desc">Your scorecard tells you what happened. Notes tell you why.</span>
          </div>
          <p class="cmd-note">
            Add freeform notes to any hole or round in the app — context on a double bogey,
            a decision that backfired, or anything worth remembering. <code class="inline">yips notes</code>
            surfaces all of them across every round. Filter by course with <code class="inline">--course &lt;name&gt;</code>.
          </p>
          <pre class="terminal output"><code>Round: Pine Valley GC  ·  2024-11-03  ·  82 (+10)  [a1b2c3d4]

Hole 7  Par 4  Index 3  412yds  Score: 6 (+2)
  Tried to cut the corner on the dogleg, pulled driver into the trees.
  Punched out sideways, chunked the third. Down the left side next time.

Hole 16  Par 4  Index 1  445yds  Score: 7 (+3)
  Three-putted from 8 feet. Mental collapse after the drive caught the rough.

---

Round: Cypress Creek CC  ·  2024-10-20  ·  79 (+7)  [b5c6d7e8]

Hole 3  Par 5  Index 9  520yds  Score: 8 (+3)
  Lost two balls in the hazard. Should have laid up off the tee.</code></pre>

          <p class="cmd-note">Use <code class="inline">yips notes &lt;id&gt;</code> to pull notes for a single round.</p>

          <p class="cmd-note">
            Add <code class="inline">--json</code> to get structured output — each note includes hole number,
            par, yardage, hole index, score, and score vs par. Enough context for an AI to find
            patterns across months of rounds:
          </p>
          <pre class="terminal"><code>yips notes --json | claude "what patterns do you see in my double bogeys or worse? what should I focus on?"</code></pre>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Flags -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Flags &amp; options</h2>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Flag</th><th>Commands</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>--profile &lt;slug&gt;</code></td>
                <td><code>round</code>, <code>stats</code>, <code>clubs</code></td>
                <td>SG benchmark profile. Valid slugs: <code>tour_pro</code>, <code>scratch</code>, <code>hcp_5</code>, <code>hcp_10</code>, <code>hcp_15</code>, <code>hcp_20</code>, <code>hcp_25</code>. Default: <code>tour_pro</code>.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>--estimate</code></td>
                <td><code>round</code>, <code>stats</code></td>
                <td>Fill GPS-missing distances from hole yardage and club averages so partial holes still show a split. Estimated cells are marked with <code>~</code>.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>--json</code></td>
                <td><code>notes</code>, <code>clubs</code>, <code>holes</code></td>
                <td>Emit raw JSON for piping into other tools.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>--course &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
                <td><code>notes</code></td>
                <td>Filter by partial, case-insensitive course name.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>Environment variables</h3>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>YIPS_TOKEN</code></td>
                <td>—</td>
                <td>Google ID token; bypasses stored credentials.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>YIPS_API_URL</code></td>
                <td><code>https://api.theyips.app</code></td>
                <td>Override the API base URL.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Pipe it anywhere -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Pipe it anywhere</h2>
        <p>
          Every command that accepts <code class="inline">--json</code> outputs clean JSON you can pipe into anything —
          a spreadsheet, a script, or an AI.
        </p>
        <pre class="terminal"><code>yips notes --json | claude "what patterns do you see in my double bogeys or worse? what should I focus on?"</code></pre>
        <pre class="terminal"><code>yips holes 'Riverbend' --json | claude "where is my club selection hurting me most?"</code></pre>
        <pre class="terminal"><code>yips clubs --json > clubs.json</code></pre>
        <pre class="terminal"><code>yips rounds | grep "Pine Valley"</code></pre>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  main { padding-bottom: 80px; }

  .hero {
    padding: 72px 0 56px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  h1 em { color: var(--green); font-style: normal; }

  .lead {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
    padding-bottom: 64px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  h2 {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .platform-badge {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--muted);
    background: var(--surface2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-left: 6px;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  /* Terminal blocks */
  .terminal {
    background: #111;
    border: 1px solid #2a2a2a;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 12px 0 20px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', 'Menlo', 'Monaco', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .terminal code { font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; }

  .terminal.output { color: #94a3b8; }

  code.inline {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--green);
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
  }

  /* Command blocks */
  .cmd-block {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .cmd-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cmd-name {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--green);
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .cmd-desc {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .cmd-note {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted2);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    max-width: 620px;
  }

  /* Tables */
  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  th {
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted2);
    padding: 8px 16px 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  td {
    padding: 10px 16px 10px 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    vertical-align: top;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  td code {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--green);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  td:first-child code { white-space: nowrap; }

  .inline-link { color: var(--green); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .inline-link:hover { opacity: 0.8; }
</style>
